description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is an exciting opportunity for a midwife to join the Birth Refelctions team and contine this valuable service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Birth Reflections plays a major role in facilitating a woman&#39;s emotional recovery following birth with two main aims; to help wmen explore their birth experience, giving the opportunity to clarity and ask question, and to identify areas the maternity services can improve care provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have excellent listening skills and be confident to explain the events of labour and birth. Have good time keeping and documentation skills, experience with social media and report writing is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recent Consultant Unit experience is desirable but we look forward to hearing what applicants feel they could contribute to the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Bex Walsh, rebekahwalsh@nhs.net, 01225 826886&lt;/p&gt;
